text: Really hope this movie flops considering how insulting it is to the actual Aokigahara forest where people actually go to end their lives. the real forest is full of signs that tell people how good life is and to think of their families. people go in there constantly volunteering to find new bodies to put them to rest. yes, the forest has a creepy air to it since people go to this secluded, peaceful area to end their own lives, but their are flowers from loved ones scattered everywhere, not malicious spirits who want to attack the living. movies like this insult the lives lost in this forest, and i for one am not going to watch it. the story idea is good, and so far the acting seems good, but they could have at least respected the memories of those who weren't strong enough to fight through a mental illness that has claimed the lives of thousands of people instead of disrespect the families of the lost by saying the souls of the fallen are now murderous beings.

text: It really sucks that they're making a movie about a REAL place where people CURRENTLY go to commit suicide. This isn't an urban legend, or part of Japan's mythos. Japan has a large mental health problem and there's a lot of stigma around depression. This film does nothing to help the people currently suffering in Japan. And it actually goes against the government's attempts to downplay the Aokigahara forest's association with suicide in order to stop locals from going there to hang themselves, overdose, etc.

I imagine the filming caused a bunch of ruckus....also, really? you're going to use white people as the main cast? I understand that this was done to appeal to a western audience, but really....looks just as stupid as any other western horror film. I hope everyone will recognize that what they did to make this film should not be taken lightly. If you agree...i strongly urge you to speak out and boycott this film....definitely would not watch this...

text: Another promising horror movie and another disappointment. This could've been very creepy , eerie and effective film, but it satisfied itself being lame, cliche, bland and less than mediocre attempt at ghost story. I liked the lead actress, you could see tention and fear all over her face in certain moments, production and locations in the movie are great, Zlatibor county in Serbia is really beautiful and it was ambitious attempt at creating something new.  The problem is that movie comes of as incoherent. It seemed like there wasn't long term planing or vision put into creating it, and it felt like they were writing the next scene while shooting another. Scares are nothing more than jump scares and it is the easiest and laziest way to go, you really do not care about these people, story and character motivation is very weak and certain parts just come out of nowhere without any explanation or resolution. Ending makes zero sense and last shot is cringeworthy. Overall THE FOREST is underwhelming and joins all other failed horror attempts like The Gallows, The Other Ones and many more. 1/5

It is also known as the suicide forest because it is a place chosen for people to comite suicide , it is reported around 100 suicides happen per year at this forest . So you could say that this forest is haunted whitout any doubt .
